creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of The National Geographic Magazine Vol. 07 - 06. June 1896 by Various.
Read in English by MaryAnnS; BettyB; Carol Cotter
The National Geographic Magazine, an illustrated monthly, the June Number.
It includes the following articles:
  • The Seine, the Meuse, and the Moselle, by William M. Davis
  • Across the Gulf by rail to Key West, by Jefferson B. Browne
  • A geographical description of the British Islands, by W. M. Davis
  • The Mexican Census
along with geographic literature, notes and miscellanea.

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
